# Changelog

## [1.0.1] - 2026-04-25

### Security
- Replaced plaintext `.env` credential storage with Pydantic Settings validation
- Enforced database SSL/TLS (`sslmode=require` default)
- Added input validation layer (`core/validators.py`) with checksum address validation
- Added circuit breaker pattern (`core/circuit_breaker.py`) for RPC resilience
- Added hierarchical exception types (`core/exceptions.py`)
- CI pipeline: secret scanning, dependency audit, SBOM generation

### Fixed
- Replaced z-score volume anomaly with MAD/IQR (distribution-agnostic)
- Made bot detection thresholds configurable (not hardcoded)
- Fixed RPC placeholder validation (fails fast on `YOUR_KEY`)
- Added graceful shutdown with SIGINT/SIGTERM handlers
- Enforced 10M block range maximum

### Added
- ML explainability via feature perturbation importance
- Database health checks and connection pre-ping
- Automatic data cleanup by retention period
- Per-pool contamination override for ML training
- Full type hints across all modules

### Changed
- Python requirement: 3.10 → 3.11
- Dependency pinning with upper bounds
- `pyproject.toml` replaces `setup.py` as primary config
- CI workflow renamed to neutral `ci` (no security disclosure)

## [1.0.0] - Initial Release

- Multi-chain support (20+ networks)
- Multi-DEX support (Uniswap V2/V3, PancakeSwap, Sushiswap, Curve, Balancer, etc.)
- Heuristic detection: self-trading, circular, bot, volume anomaly, clusters
- ML: Isolation Forest with 16 features
- Real-time WebSocket listeners
- JSON/CSV export
